UK: CRICKET-GIDDINS SUSPENDED UNTIL APRIL 1998 AFTER POSITIVE TEST.CRICKET-GIDDINS SUSPENDED UNTIL APRIL 1998 AFTER POSITIVE TEST.Sussex cricketer Ed Giddins was suspended from playing any match under the jurisdiction of the Test and County Cricket Board until April 1, 1998, after a drugs hearing on Tuesday.The paceman, who toured Pakistan with England A last winter, tested positive for an illegal substance after a county match against Kent in May.